Most relevant reviews












by
coachgund
Oct 06, 2008


Fick's Book is Good!
Fick's book is a good read. I did prefer Evan Wright's Generation Kill a little bit more because it covered a wider scope of personalities and soldiers. Fick's book is very comprehensive and goes into great detail of what a leader of men in battle must deal with on a daily basis. If you liked the Generation Kill Book/TV Series you will probably like Fick's book as well, I did. Fick's book is more strategic and written from  a command/leadership point of view compared to Wright's book which is just written by a regular guy but a guy who writes for a living so it is probably a little more entertaining than Fick's book for  the average/nonmilitary reader like myself.

X



Previous image






Next image
















(0)





(0)



















by
hotfire247
Sep 13, 2008


Great read....No questions!!
I first heard of Fick in Generation Kill. When I found that Fick had a book out himself I bought it without reading any reviews and have not been disappointed!! I have yet to put the book down and am appreciative of an author that writes with such truth and honesty. It is simply put.... a great read!

X



