    Fick is an excellent writer, and conveys a side of war not ...
  

    &#34;One Bullet Away&#34; provides a well-written and thoughtful counterpoint to &#34;Generation Kill&#34; (which, let's face it, is the reason 90% of readers picked up this book).Fick is an excellent writer, and conveys a side of war not often seen, including an interesting insight into some of the confusion and tension immediately following the September 11 attacks.On top of that, he's only mildly self-aggrandizing, a rare enough trait in any autobiography, let alone a military one.
  

