There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.5.0 out of 5 starsMore Than A Combat MemoirByNightRangeron July 21, 2014Format: Kindle Edition|Verified PurchaseThis story of one Marine officer’s transition from Ivy League college kid to thoroughly squared away combat leader is worth the read on many levels. Fick’s sense of duty leads him to join the Corps’ PLC training between his junior and senior year. He seeks a challenge and quickly finds it especially after 911 when the training ceases and it becomes a real war.Fick’s account of combat, its after effects and his riflemen’s reaction to it are well-written and put the reader there. He is unafraid to criticize the bad leadership he saw as well as salute the bravery of the kids ordered to fight in this misguided attempt at nation building. His description of combat deaths is sympathetic without being maudlin.This book is worth the read for the grunts among us. Fick’s attitude about measuring up and seeking a challenge will surely resonate with those of us who had the same questions in the middle 1960’s.0Comment|
