There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.5.0 out of 5 starsAn unusual military adventureByChuck Ashfordon May 17, 2014Format: Kindle Edition|Verified PurchaseIntrospective may be the best description of this military adventure book.  Throughout the plot, there is an strong undercurrent of exactly why the military does things the way they do.  How they build strong soldiers, how the civilian world really has no concept of this process, and why the civilian world does not really want to know.The "one bullet" analogy is introduced early and it sticks in the readers mind as the adventure unfolds.  The conclusion of the book avoids triteness.  Things are not wrapped up in a neat bundle.  Rather just the opposite, very similar to the situation many of our military heroes must experience upon returning home from combat.An unusual read, well worth your time.0Comment|
